'''Riboga's Barge''' was a [[Sail barge/Legends|barge]] that had once been owned by [[Riboga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. When the Hutt lost control of the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system's]] crime to [[Nirama]], he hastily sold off many of his possessions. A pair of [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshans]] bought his barge and converted it into the preeminent [[Casino/Legends|casino]] of [[Tolea Biqua]]. The Trandoshans had a history of bad blood with the Hutts, and found the opportunity to buy the Hutt's barge too rich to pass up on.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

The barge was divided into two sections&mdash;a paid public area and a more exclusive members only section. The members area not only had the high stakes game, but luxury lounges. The Hutt's bathing pool had been converted into a large hottub, and his never-used [[Reproduction/Legends|breeding]] chamber had been turned into a sarcastically named "Museum of Useless Inventions."<ref name="LFC" />

One of Riboga's previous employees in the barge, [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiator]] and waiter [[Bez]], was employed by the Trandoshan as a dealer for the public area.<ref name="LFC" />

